INSERT INTO `T_Comments` VALUES ('05/03/24/3468480','05/03/12/9743573','Julie McLaren','robert_stuart_mclaren@hotmail.com','','Suggestion - Enable families to sign up for a monthly donation by credit card or automatic payment from their checking account.  Committing to a $50-100 monthly donation doesn\\\'t seem so  horrendous, and far more realistic for those who have a monthly budget to work with.  It would give some families, who just don\\\'t have $600-900 lying around in the bank, to contribute to this important cause.','wbar3.sjo1-4-11-015-076.sjo1.dsl-verizon.net','2005-03-24 08:57:48',20050324085748,'05/03/12/9743573');
INSERT INTO `T_Comments` VALUES ('05/03/25/5896654','05/03/13/4495777','Mark Cokes','mcokes@adobe.com','','My concern is that i do not hear parents in other school districts being asked to make such a large donation. Last year free school transport was removed (again unheard of in all my contacts), this year we are asked to donate close on $1000, what will it be next year? All this on top of what appears to be complete lack of management regarding the building of the new middle school. The sad fact is that my son will be starting middle school next year and will be forced to attend class in portacabins - not the new school we were promised nearly two years ago. I am expected to pay for this?\r\n\r\nIn the end i will pay as to not do so will, i believe, directly affect our sons education. But how can i be sure that this crisis is not due to mismanagement and that i am not just throwing money into a pot that will run dry again?','wbar3.sjo1-4-11-012-192.sjo1.dsl-verizon.net','2005-03-25 21:44:56',20050325214456,'05/03/13/4495777');
INSERT INTO `T_Comments` VALUES ('05/03/31/4780871','05/03/12/9512474','Katie Jeffery','katie.jeffery@verizon.net','','It\\\'s obvious that this amount of money is needed to keep the programs listed above. Our family is in full support but we have an important question. If the $280,000 is not received by the end of this campaign, will our school be deprived of these exact programs? If so, does that mean there will be NO music, NO art and NOT the right amount of yard duty aids, NO small class sizes. These are all HUGE issues for us in considering our kids education. What if the monetary goal is not met? Thank you, Katie','wbar3.sjo1-4.26.131.194.sjo1.dsl-verizon.net','2005-03-31 13:33:00',20050331133300,'05/03/12/9512474');
