Verdana\'> </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>FINANCE COMMITTEE/TREASURER (Gerald O&#8217;Regan, 353-8313, </span></b></p> <p class=MsoNormal style=\'text-indent:.5in\'><b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt; font-family:Verdana\'><a href=\"mailto:Grgn@chevron.com\">Grgn@chevron.com</a>)</span></b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'> </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'> </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>ADMINISTRATIVE, LIAISON AND FUNDING COMMITTEE </span></b></p> <p class=MsoNormal style=\'margin-left:.5in\'><b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt; font-family:Verdana\'>(Lydia Dobyns, 353-2433, <a href=\"mailto:Lydia@Dobyns.com\">Lydia@Dobyns.com</a>, Pat McGrath, 353-2144, <a href=\"mailto:pkmcgrath@aol.com\">pkmcgrath@aol.com</a>, Julie Gouldsbury, 353-8223, <a href=\"mailto:Julie@gouldsberry.com\">Julie@gouldsberry.com</a>)</span></b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'> </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">      </span><span style=\'mso-tab-count:1\'>    </span>In general this committee will manage all activities associated with getting LPEF funds to the district </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'> </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>PR/COMMUNICATION COMMITTEE<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">  </span>(Joan Hoffman, 353-5088, <a href=\"mailto:JMH4@inreach.com\">JMH4@inreach.com</a>)</span></b></p> <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=\'font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'> </span></b></p> <p class=MsoBodyText2>If you are willing to work with us over the summer, please contact Pat McGrath, Julie Gouldsbury or Lydia Dobyns</p> <p class=MsoNormal><span style=\'font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt\'> </span></p> <p class=MsoNormal><b><span style=\'font-size:14.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt; font-family:Verdana\'>Thank you!',0,336,3,'barry','','2099-12-31 23:59:59','1');
INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (7,'barry','History of LPEF','2001-09-21 14:06:46','How We Came To Be Here Tonight (Loma Public Education Fund). ','  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <![if !supportEmptyParas]> <![endif]><o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P class=MsoBodyTextIndent3>\r\n  It started rather innocently, in February 2001, first over breakfast at the\r\n  Los Gatos Café, then over coffee and treats from Gayle&#8217;s. &#8220;What\r\n  can we do about the teacher salary conflict?&#8221; &#8220;Why does our district\r\n  pay so much less than other Santa Clara school districts?&#8221;\r\n  &#8220;Don&#8217;t we get enough funding to pay competitive salaries, have\r\n  programs to augment classroom learning, keep roofs from leaking and stop\r\n  the gophers from making our playfields dangerous for sports?&#8221; And\r\n  ultimately, &#8220;What are other school districts doing differently? How\r\n  are they affording programs, better salaries and safe\r\n  structures?&#8221;<o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <![if !supportEmptyParas]> <![endif]><o:p></o:p>Four women connected\r\n  by a deep sense of urgency and a desire to make changes for the better searched\r\n  for a new idea. They were all moms of children in Loma Prieta schools. All\r\n  busy women, whose lives had little room for a new, huge commitment. And yet,\r\n  despite the nervous feeling in their collective guts, the wish for something\r\n  better prevailed: A shared-vision for excellent education for their children\r\n  and their neighbors&#8217; children. And, even more importantly than the vision,\r\n  a willingness to make the dream real by creating an organization strong enough\r\n  to be a lasting legacy for the community they loved and appreciated.\r\n  <o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <![if !supportEmptyParas]> The outreach started. Phone calls were placed.\r\n  The call for help was always preceded by conversations explaining the need,\r\n  the vision and the promise that no volunteer would tackle huge tasks alone,\r\n  and that we would make the work fun while always focusing on the desired\r\n  results.<o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <![if !supportEmptyParas]> The response was heart-warming. The four\r\n  women were soon joined by a fifth, and the core group was born: Lydia, Amy,\r\n  Sandy, Cathy and Pat. Meetings were scheduled. Homes were opened to host\r\n  group discussions. Parents came together to consider the vision. The call\r\n  for volunteers was issued, again and again. By April the Loma Public Education\r\n  Fund had its first Executive Steering committee. Five people became ten women\r\n  and one man when Julie, Celia, Jeannie, Gerald, Michelle and Joan signed\r\n  on. In May we made a presentation to the Loma Prieta Board of Trustees. Before\r\n  school ended in June we had more than 50 people who had agreed to help produce\r\n  a summer pledge drive, solicit donations for a benefit auction, produce an\r\n  October gala to showcase the auction, create an administrative structure\r\n  to weave the activities together, and work to create partnerships with school\r\n  administrators and teachers.<o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <![if !supportEmptyParas]> You are here tonight as testament to love,\r\n  support, caring and the power of what is possible by working together. We\r\n  want to say a special &#8216;thank you&#8217; to our families, for allowing\r\n  us to devote days, nights and many weekends to this cause. Without the support\r\n  provided by our spouses and children, none of our accomplishments would be\r\n  possible. From the bottoms of our hearts we thank you and invite you to continue\r\n  with us on this journey to turn our schools into the very best they can be\r\n  for all our children. <o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P class=MsoHeader style=\'tab-stops:.5in\'>\r\n  <![if !supportEmptyParas]> <![endif]><o:p></o:p>\r\n  <P ALIGN=Center>\r\n  <IMG SRC=\"themes/lpef/img/signature.jpg\" WIDTH=\"576\" HEIGHT=\"154\" BORDER=\"0\" ALIGN=\"Middle\">\r\n  <P ALIGN=Left>\r\n',0,315,5,'barry','','2099-12-31 23:59:59','1');
INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (16,'barry','LPEF Information Sheet','2001-05-09 22:47:51','A Brief Introduction to the Loma Public Education Fund','<TABLE border=1>\r\n  <TR>\r\n    <TD width=\"50%\" valign=\"top\"><B>Mission:</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      The Loma Public Education Fund (LPEF) is a non-profit organization of volunteers\r\n      committed to raise money to enhance the educational experience for students\r\n      in the Loma Prieta Joint Union School District.\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>Why do we need an Education Fund?</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      Founded in early 2001, a group of parents banded together to raise significant\r\n      money on an annual basis to preserve and enhance the District\'s ability to\r\n      offer outstanding educational programs as a vital part of the student experience.\r\n      <P>\r\n      By raising funds for educational programs, the District can reallocate funds\r\n      to staff compensation, thus retaining current teachers and making our District\r\n      attractive for new teachers.\r\n      <P>\r\n      <P>\r\n       </TD>\r\n    <TD valign=\"top\"><B>Our goal is simple: raise money!</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      The Fund serves solely to raise money. Fund members meet regularly with the\r\n      superintendent, principals, teachers and parents to develop funding priorities.\r\n      Monies are awarded as specific grants to the District, which include\r\n      accountability requirements and measurement criteria\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>Donations are 100% tax deductible.</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      The Fund operates as a separate arm of the Loma Prieta Community Foundation\r\n      (LPCF), with its own Executive and Operating Steering committees. LPCF is\r\n      a 501.3c corporation and all donations to the Education Fund are tax deductible.\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>Funding Philosophy:</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      The LPEF believes that the best educational experience is one that blends\r\n      academics, the arts and sports. It is our goal to work with the District\r\n      to develop coordinated funding strategies that best benefit our students.\r\n      <P>\r\n       </TD>\r\n  </TR>\r\n  <TR>\r\n    <TD width=\"50%\" valign=\"top\"><B>The LPEF Executive Steering Committee adopts\r\n      funding priorities and conducts annual assessments of all program grants.\r\n      </B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>Types of programs to fund:</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      Following are kinds of programs and services the Fund may support:\r\n      <OL>\r\n      <LI>\r\n          reading intervention\r\n      <LI>\r\n          math and science intervention\r\n     <LI>\r\n          music and art instructors\r\n <LI>\r\n          counseling interns\r\n        <LI>\r\n          librarians\r\n        <LI>\r\n          curriculum alignment for K-8\r\n      <LI>\r\n          physical education/sports specialists\r\n     <LI>\r\n          computer and software\r\n     <LI>\r\n          technology personnel\r\n      </OL>\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>Fund Raising Objectives:</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      Contribute $100,000 or more during the 2001 - 2002 school year by:\r\n      <UL>\r\n  <LI>\r\n          Conducting a sponsorship drive, attracting more than half of the District\'s\r\n        parents.\r\n  <LI>\r\n          Holding a first annual October gala dinner and auction. Mark your calendar\r\n          for October 6th, 2001!\r\n      </UL>\r\n      <P>\r\n    </TD>\r\n    <TD valign=\"top\"><B>We need your help!</B>\r\n      <UL>\r\n   <LI>\r\n          Join today. There are four suggested donor levels ranging from $250 to $5,000.\r\n      Checks should be made to: Loma Public Education Fund and mailed to: LPEF,\r\n   23800 Summit Road, Los Gatos, CA 95033\r\n    <LI>\r\n          Donate items for the auction.\r\n     <LI>\r\n          Volunteer to be part of this exciting organization.\r\n      </UL>\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>What do I do next?</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      Contact anyone of the following people to make a donation, become a corporate\r\n      sponsor and/or find out how you can volunteer.\r\n      <P>\r\n      <B>LPEF Executive Steering Committee:</B>\r\n      <P>\r\n      Lydia Dobyns, 353-2433,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:lydia@dobyns.com\">lydia@dobyns.com</A> <BR>\r\n      Julie Gouldsberry, 353-8223, \r\n      <A href=\"mailto:julie@gouldsberry.com\">julie@gouldsberry.com</A> <BR>\r\n      Joan Hoffman, 353-5088,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:jmh4@inreach.com\">jmh4@inreach.com</A> <BR>\r\n      Cathy Lanagan, 353-8384,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:cnlanagan@aol.com\">cnlanagan@aol.com</A><BR>\r\n      Celia Maddox, 353-5973,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:celiam2@attglobal.net\">celiam2@attglobal.net</A> <BR>\r\n      Michelle McAuliffe, 353-9080,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:michelle@laseraid.net\">michelle@laseraid.net</A> <BR>\r\n      Pat McGrath, 353-2144,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:pkmcgrath@aol.com\">pkmcgrath@aol.com</A> <BR>\r\n      Jean Niemann, 353-5625,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:niemann.six@verizon.net\">niemann.six@verizon.net</A> <BR>\r\n      Gerald O\'Regan, 353-8313,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:grgn@chevron.com\">grgn@chevron.com</A> <BR>\r\n      Amy Weingarten, 353-8820,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:aweingflo@yahoo.com\">aweingflo@yahoo.com</A><BR>\r\n      Sandy Whitney, 353-1044,\r\n      <A href=\"mailto:casadelasol@yahoo.com\">casadelasol@yahoo.com</A></TD>\r\n  </TR>\r\n</TABLE>',0,354,3,'barry','','2099-12-31 23:59:59','1');
INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (6,'barry','2001-2002 Funding Priorities','2001-06-15 11:52:35',' We believe strong teacher support and involvement is\r\n  vital to Loma Public Education Fund&#146;s success. We want to be ready with\r\n  new programs at the beginning of the 2001-2002 year. We anticipate reaching\r\n  our fundraising target by the end of October. So, what are the best ways\r\n  to utilize $100,000 next year to enhance the educational experience for our\r\n  students? ','  <P>\r\n  <BR clear=ALL>\r\n<SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>&nbsp;We&#146;ve\r\n  heard from parents, and potential corporate donors, that the more specific\r\n  our program goals are the easier it will be to exceed our $100,000. We are\r\n  preparing letters that will go to parents in the next few weeks asking for\r\n  their financial support by participating in our first annual pledge drive.\r\n  Additionally a volunteer team will phone parents as a follow-up to the letter\r\n  (yes, during the summer!). </SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal style=\'margin-left:.25in\'>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>Our preliminary thoughts for 2001-2002 funding center\r\n  around three themes:</SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal style=\'margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list 1.0in\'>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;\r\n\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>1.<SPAN style=\'font:7.0pt \"Times New Roman\"\'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n  </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>There is strong support in the parent community for\r\n  core academic programs that benefit most students.</SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal style=\'margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list 1.0in\'>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;\r\n\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>2.<SPAN style=\'font:7.0pt \"Times New Roman\"\'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n  </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>A desire to develop high standards for every student\r\n  and closing the &#147;achievement gap&#148; between various groups of students\r\n  </SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal style=\'margin-left:1.0in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo2;\r\ntab-stops:list 1.0in\'>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;\r\n\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>3.<SPAN style=\'font:7.0pt \"Times New Roman\"\'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n  </SPAN></SPAN><SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>Working with the District to ensure current programs\r\n  in developmental PE, the Arts, Library services and technology are maintained\r\n  (and possibly enhanced).</SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>&nbsp;Since\r\n  this is our first funding cycle (both raising and disbursing money), we&#146;re\r\n  definitely in learning mode! Next year we anticipate fielding parent and\r\n  teacher surveys to help assess the effectiveness of our first slate of programs\r\n  funded and to help us identify priorities and opportunities for the 2002-2003\r\n  year.</SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>&nbsp;Here\r\n  are the funding guidelines LPEF has adopted. Ideally every program funded\r\n  by LPEF will meet all the following criteria </SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;\r\n\r\nfont-family:Verdana\'>&nbsp;</SPAN>\r\n  <UL style=\'margin-top:0in\' type=disc>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>Promotes\r\n      excellence </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>Is\r\n      meaningful to all targeted students </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>Enough\r\n      is being spent to make the program worthwhile </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>It\'s\r\n      measurable </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>Has\r\n      long term development benefits </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>Helps\r\n      support district goals </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>Promotes\r\n      a well-rounded student</SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>There\r\n      are adequate district and/or site personnel resources and commitments to\r\n      support the program </SPAN>\r\n    <LI class=MsoNormal style=\'mso-list:l2 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in\'>\r\n      <SPAN style=\'font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana\'>There\r\n      are limited or no alternative resources to support the\r\n      program</SPAN>\r\n  </UL>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal style=\'margin-left:.25in\'>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-family:Verdana\'>&nbsp;</SPAN>\r\n  <P class=MsoNormal>\r\n  <SPAN style=\'font-family:Verdana\'>&nbsp;</SPAN>\r\n</DIV>\r\n',0,301,3,'barry','','2099-12-31 23:59:59','1');
