INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (14,'barry','LPEF Announcement Letter in MNN','2001-02-14 22:42:07','Parents Launch Loma Prieta C.T. English Educational Foundation to Raise Money for Local Schools','<p >Submitted by: Lydia and Barry Dobyns, Cathy and Doug\r\nLanagan, <br>\r\nAmy and Steve Weingarten, and Sandy and Bern Whitney\r\n<br>Feb 14, 2001\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >As parents of Loma Prieta students we believe our community\r\nplaces a high value on our schools, and further we believe it is district\r\nemployees who are the primary key to the quality of education our children\r\nexperience.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">  </span>We dont want to have to\r\nchoose between teacher salaries and small classrooms, or between developmental\r\nP.E. and the computer lab, or between playing fields with dangerous gopher\r\nholes or roofs that leak. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >As a community we are just now discovering the challenges of\r\nthe current budget and we want to take action. Funds raised through the parcel\r\ntax clearly have a very positive impact in the form of reduced class sizes, and\r\nadditional programs. The home and school clubs also do a great job of raising\r\nmoney for school-specific projects and programs. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >However, despite these efforts, there is still a need for\r\nadditional money to enable the district to spend more of its general fund on\r\nimproving salaries.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >We are announcing our intent to form the Loma Prieta C.T.\r\nEnglish Educational Foundation (LPCTEEF), whose primary purpose is to raise\r\nmoney, annually, to augment district revenues. We expect to raise at least\r\n$50,000 for the next school year through a variety of fund raising\r\navenues.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">  </span>We are following the examples\r\nof the very successful Los Gatos Educational Foundation (<a\r\nhref=\"http://www.lgeef.org/\">www.lgeef.org</a>), The Saratoga Education\r\nFoundation (<a href=\"http://www.saratoga-sef.org/\">www.saratoga-sef.org</a>) and the Menlo\r\nPark-Atherton Education Foundation (<a href=\"http://www.mpaef.org/\">www.mpaef.org</a>).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >We have begun discussions with the Loma Prieta Community\r\nFoundation, and are hopeful that we will be able to house this effort under the\r\nauspices of the LPCF.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >We are confident that we will enjoy the strong support of\r\nparents and the mountain community. In fact, given the current negotiations\r\nimpasse within the district, we wish to launch the LPCTEEF <b><i>now</i></b>\r\nand pledge an immediate contribution of at least $20,000, thanks to a generous\r\nanonymous contribution.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">  </span>Our goal is to\r\nsecure additional donations of at least $11,000, which will result in a minimum\r\ncontribution of $31,000, or the equivalent of a 1% salary increase for district\r\npersonnel this year. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >We also support placing a June ballot initiative before the\r\nvoters for a new parcel tax to create ongoing source of revenues to maintain programs\r\nand pay higher salaries. We view our fundraising efforts as complimentary to a\r\nnew parcel tax. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p >We hope you will join us in helping focus current community\r\nconcerns towards finding additional sources of revenue to improve our\r\nchildren\'s education. Help us work together as a team to recognize not only the\r\nvalue of each and every child in the Loma Prieta district, but also to\r\nrecognize the invaluable contributions of each and every adult entrusted with\r\neducating that child. To find out how you can help, please call Cathy Lanagan\r\n(353-8384), Amy Weingarten (353-8820) or Sandy Whitney (353-1044) or \r\nemail Lydia Dobyns <a href=\"mailto:lydia@dobyns.com\">Lydia@Dobyns.com</a>.\r\n',0,572,3,'barry','','2003-06-20 23:59:59','1');
INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (15,'barry','Open Letter to Loma Prieta Joint Unified School District Board of Trustees','2001-02-09 22:45:09','Dear LPJUSD Board of Trustees ...','<p>February 9, 2001\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLoma Prieta Joint Union School District <br>\r\nBoard of Trustees<br>\r\n23800 Summit Road<br>\r\nLos Gatos, CA 95033\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Dear Board of Trustees:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>As parents of Loma Prieta students we believe our community\r\nplaces a high value on our schools, and further we believe it is district\r\nemployees who are the primary key to the quality of education our children\r\nexperience.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">  </span>We dont want to have to\r\nchoose between teacher salaries and small classrooms, or between developmental\r\nP.E. and the computer lab, or between playing fields with dangerous gopher\r\nholes or roofs that leak. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>As a community we are just now discovering the challenges of\r\nthe current budget and we want to take action. Funds raised through the parcel\r\ntax clearly have a very positive impact in the form of reduced class sizes, and\r\nadditional programs. The home and school clubs also do a great job of raising\r\nmoney for school-specific projects and programs. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>However, despite these efforts, there is still a need for\r\nadditional money to enable the district to spend more of its general fund on\r\nimproving salaries.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We are writing you to announce our intent to form the Loma\r\nPrieta and C.T. English Educational Foundation (LPCTEEF), whose primary purpose\r\nis to raise money, annually, to augment district revenues. We expect to raise\r\nat least $50,000 for the next school year through a variety of fund raising\r\navenues. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We have begun discussions with the Loma Prieta Community\r\nFoundation, and are hopeful that we will be able to house this effort under the\r\nauspices of the LPCF. Most other school districts with similar parent values\r\nhave established very successful foundations that have enabled school districts\r\nto spend more of the districts revenues on salaries without gutting programs\r\nor services.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We are confident that we will enjoy the strong support of\r\nparents and the mountain community. In fact, given the current negotiations\r\nimpasse within the district, we wish to launch the LPCTEEF now and pledge an\r\nimmediate contribution of at least $20,000, thanks to a generous anonymous\r\ncontribution.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">  </span>Our goal is to secure\r\nadditional donations of at least $11,000, which will result in a minimum\r\ncontribution of $31,000, or the equivalent of a 1% salary increase for district\r\npersonnel this year. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We also support placing a June ballot initiative before the\r\nvoters for a new parcel tax to create ongoing source of revenues to maintain\r\nprograms and pay higher salaries. We view our fundraising efforts as\r\ncomplimentary to a new parcel tax. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>We hope you will join us in helping focus current community\r\nconcerns towards finding additional sources of revenue to improve our\r\nchildren\'s education. Help us work together as a team to recognize not only the\r\nvalue of each and every child in the Loma Prieta district, but also to\r\nrecognize the invaluable contributions of each and every adult entrusted with\r\neducating that child.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>Sincerely,\r\n<p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=\"100%\">\r\n<tr><td>Lydia and Barry Dobyns, </td>\r\n<td>Cathy and Doug Lanagan, </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>   </td><td>   </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>   </td><td>   </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>Amy and Steve Weingarten</td>\r\n<td>Sandy and Bern Whitney </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>   </td><td>   </td></tr>\r\n<tr><td>   </td><td>   </td></tr>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>',0,296,3,'barry','','2003-06-20 23:59:59','1');
INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (38,'lydia','Tickets Now on Sale for 2004 Gala/Auction','2004-06-14 10:50:55','Get Your Tickets Today for the 2004 Gala!','The Loma Public Education Fund (LPEF) is pleased to announce that tickets are now available for purchase for the fourth annual gala, dinner and auction to be held Saturday, October 2, 2004.  One Enchanted Evening IV will begin at 4:00 pm. Bill and Patti Hughes have once again, graciously donated Mason du Lac for this exciting fundraising event which last year raised almost $50,000 for programs for Loma Prieta and CT English schools. \n\nLPEF continues to provide critical financial support for many school programs including Reading Recovery, Middle School Math Club, and Student Counseling. New for next year is a program grant that will protect current elective offerings at CT English, and allow the creation of a zero period and new choices during the regular school day. None of the LPEF program grants would be possible without the generous support and donations we receive from our community and beyond.\n\nOne Enchanted Evening is a wonderful community event that provides an opportunity to enjoy an evening out with friends, family and neighbors while helping our local schools.   Its a night to embrace our beautiful mountain and remember why we choose to live here. The event is fun, lively and the auction offers fantastic items including tickets to the SF Giants and 49er, great vacation getaways, wonderful wine, gift certificates to Los Gatos merchants, art, jewelry and much more.\n\nTo purchase tickets visit: print an order form, or stop by the district office for an order form, or call 408/566-3007.  The price is $75.00 per ticket, which includes dinner, live music and the auction. With every $75 ticket you will receive $12.50 in Gala Bucks.  Gala Bucks can be used to buy auction items, raffle tickets or mystery table items.  \n\nPlan now to attend this magical event.  If you have items to donate to the auction, please call 566-3007. It is great fun to get a group of friends and family together to sit at a table. \n ',0,331,2,'lydia','','2004-10-10 23:59:59','0');
