INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (17,'barry','Print a Pledge Form','2001-08-24 22:51:29','<center>LPEF Pledge Form</center>','<P ALIGN=Center>\r\n<IMG SRC=\"themes/lpef/img/LPFFLogo.gif\" WIDTH=\"318\" HEIGHT=\"171\" ALT=\"L\'peef Logo\"><BR>\r\n<I><SMALL>Giving our children the education they deserve.</SMALL></I>\r\n<P align=center >\r\n<BIG><BIG><B>Pledge Form</B></BIG></BIG>\r\n<P >\r\n<SMALL>Contributing is easy. Just mail the completed form with your\r\ncheck to the address below, or drop it off at the District Office. \r\nMany companies encourage philanthropy through matching gift programs. \r\nIf your company offers this opportunity, attach a completed match form with\r\nyour payment and we will do the rest.  Thank you for your dedication\r\nand generosity.  We can\'t do it without you.<BR>\r\n</SMALL>\r\n<UL type=disc>\r\n  <LI>\r\n    <SMALL>Friend             \r\n    $25-$499</SMALL>\r\n  <LI>\r\n    <SMALL>Associate        \r\n    $500-$999</SMALL>\r\n  <LI>\r\n    <SMALL>Partner            \r\n    $1,000-$4999</SMALL>\r\n  <LI>\r\n    <SMALL>Benefactor        $5,000 or\r\n    more</SMALL>\r\n</UL>\r\n<P>\r\n<B><I><SMALL>The following information will appear in our annual program\r\nexactly as completed:</SMALL></I></B>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>Name________________________________________________________</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>Address______________________________________________________</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>Phone________________________________________________________</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>Email (optional)________________________________________________</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL> I prefer this donation be anonymous:____________(check here)</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>Donor Amount:</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>  $_____ Friend  $_____Associate  $______Partner \r\n$_____Benefactor  $_____Other</SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>  Please make check payable to:  <B>Loma Public Education Fund</B></SMALL>\r\n<P>\r\n<SMALL>  <B>You may drop off the form and check at the District Office\r\nor Mail to:</B></SMALL>\r\n<P ALIGN=Center>\r\n<B><SMALL> LPEF<BR>\r\n23800 Summit Road<BR>\r\nLos Gatos, CA  95033</SMALL></B>\r\n<P ALIGN=Center>\r\n<I><SMALL>  Loma Public Education Fund is a 501(c)3, Non-Profit\r\nCorporation, Tax ID# 03-0440872</SMALL></I>\r\n',0,339,2,'barry','','2099-12-31 23:59:59','1');
INSERT INTO `lpef_stories` VALUES (30,'lydia','LPEF Grants Support Every Student','2002-09-17 01:00:47','As community members and parents, each of us has been asked to contribute money and time to LPEF.  Often parents ask, \"How will my child benefit?\" This important question is a primary consideration for LPEF members as we work with the District to determine funding priorities.  Our goal is to make program awards that help all students better reach their full potential.  ','The District (the Board of Trustees, Administrators and Staff) identify program opportunities and develop specific grant requests for LPEF. LPEF encourages the district to develop two kinds of programs: those that directly benefit all students as well as small group intervention programs which indirectly support all students through a \"ripple effect.\" \n\nReading Recovery (RR) is an example of a small group intervention program that has started an enormous \"ripple\".  While only 12-20, first graders directly participate in this program annually; every first grader is assessed to identify those who would most benefit from Reading Recovery. These assessments provide valuable teaching insights for the first grade teachers. As RR students progress the overall classroom reading level increases, allowing teachers to teach at a more advanced curriculum level.  This full class \"ripple\" effect has carried over into the second grade this year. As a result, this \'learning readiness\' will increase every year that RR is offered.  Teachers at CTE are enthusiastic supporters of LPEF\'s investment in RR. \n\nGiven LPEF\'s long-term vision and district-wide mission we are confident that our commitment to RR will fundamentally improve the quality of education for every student from last year onward. Another \"positive ripple\" according to Superintendent and Principal Mary Ellen Lewis Johnson are the staff development benefits RR techniques provide. As teaching concepts are shared and new strategies and assessments for working with children in the areas of reading, writing, and spelling are introduced, the entire staff becomes more effective.  \n\nThe other types of grants that LPEF strongly endorses are school-wide programs. Last year we funded school-wide Reading Enrichment at CTE.  Every teacher was given training and materials and assigned a group of students, arranged by reading level. The goal was to help the groups improve reading comprehension. This year LPEF has expanded the award to include a school wide math component.  We also expect to fund expanded counseling services at both schools.  Ms. Lewis-Johnson noted that having adequate counseling services helps improve the \"climate\" of both schools. Benefits of student counseling go well beyond the individual student receiving services-it tends to improve classroom and schoolyard interactions.  \n\nOther programs the district has asked LPEF to fund include purchasing sets of classroom texts, optional 7th period extra curriculum programs at CTE which may include writing, music, and open gym days; and a computer/technology staff person to work directly with Loma teachers to provide computer skills support.  IHS has requested funding for computer equipment and a reading remediation program to provide staff and parent development in teaching reading skills and identifying reading problems.\n\nSo the next time you hear about an LPEF-funded program, please know that each program award has met this simple criteria: spending money on this program can be shown to help every student either directly or indirectly. Our goal is to enhance the educational experience for all children in our District.  With your continued support LPEF can achieve this wonderful vision.\n ',0,330,3,'lydia','','2099-12-31 23:59:59','0');
